The paper discusses methods for improving AI planning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of machine learning techniques to automatically learn and extract structural information from a domain is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of macro-operators, which are a common technique in planning (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of engineering enhancements to improve the performance of the planner, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE).
